:: action-drive-to-lancaster-farm
You leave the abandoned police station and drive south to [[County Road 66->loc-county-road-6]].

You wonder if it's a holiday because you haven't seen anyone or any moving cars. You have passed houses, mostly in need of repair, but no signos of life. Perhaps there is a local festival or some other event that has drawn all the people.

You pass a video store, sitting alone in an empty, damaged parking lot. The store window is dark.

You approach a church but it too seems deserted, the parking lot empty and the doors closed.
There is a sign near the road that reads:
Ephrata Church of the Brethen
Take the Lenten Pledge

Lenten? You think to yourself. You recall something about lent being a religious observance before Easter where people give up something they like for a period of time. You wonder what people in this town might give up.

You turn east on County Road 66 and you approach what must be the [[Lancaster Farm->loc-lancaster-farm]].

You pull into the driveway. You note a few cars but you don't see anyone, not even a barking dog coming to greet you. It is late afternoon but there is still enough light that you can't tell if any lights are on in the house or if it too is abandoned.

There is a large porch that extends from the front door across the front of the house before wrapping around the West side of the house and extending to the North side.

You exit your vehicle, take one last look around and then [[step onto the large wraparound porch.->action-start-chapter-porch]]

:: action-start-chapter-porch 
<<set $chapter to "porch">>

You knock on the old wooden door and wait.

No response.

You listen for a moment. There is no sound from inside the house or even from the surrounding area. You are listening carefully even as you wait.

You knock on the door a second time. You try to peer into the house, through the window next to the door, but the curtains are drawn. The door has circular window but the glass in dingy and it is dark inside. You almost think you can see something when suddenly you hear [[something->object-sound-of-a-polaroid-camera]].

It was not loud, it was faint and you are unsure of what it was. You look behind you and to your left and right. Then you knock again, harder, more loud.

It is as the door stops resonating from your knock that you hear a new sound. Louder - like a screen door shutting.

You walk quickly along the porch and around the corner. You can see there is another door at the end of the porch and it seems to be ajar. But more importantly, you see a figure running away, disappearing around the Northwest corner of the house.

This triggers your instincts and you leap into [[pursuit->action-pursuit-1]].

:: action-pursuit-1

You race to the end of the porch and jump off the steps into what must be the backyard. There is a pool in the center of the yard and you are forced to run around it, past a small structure in the back of the pool - it is probably a poolhouse. You hurry past it and find a path.

The path leads East and, looking in that direction, you feel you see motion at the end of the path. It must be the figure you saw from before so you [[continue the pursuit->action-pursuit-2]]

:: action-pursuit-2

You run along the path and it opens up into a small clearing. You see a barn, a shed and a dirt road that heads back South.  In back of these strucutres are some sort of crop. Your hunch is that the figure either entered the shed, the barn or it is escaping along the dirt road. 

Your first bet is the shed, but it is locked. You decide to enter the barn as the door is open. You stop 10 feet into the barn, you are surrounded by hay bales and farming equipment. You look around but don't see anyone and you don't hear anything. 

Regretfully, you conclude that the mysterious figure must have slipped away down the dirt road.

You are beginning to tire but you jog back out of the barn and start [[along the dirt road.->action-pursuit-3]]

:: action-pursuit-3

The dirt road is narrow and flanked by tall crops on either side. You push forward, your footsteps muffled by the soft earth beneath you. Looking ahead, you are sure this dirt road will end on the main road, County Road 66, and you are correct. You see what must be the Lancaster's mailbox near theyir driveway.

A check along the main road shows no sign of the mysterious figure. Your patrol vehicle is parked not far away. There is no sign of anyone. 

You catch your breath while you survey the area again, looking for anywhere the figure might hide. You don't see anything.
[[Continue->action-pursuit-4]]

:: action-pursuit-4 

You slowly walk up the front stairs and onto the porch and then along the porch until it takes you back to where you first saw the mysterious figure. You are back where you started.
You approach the side door and find that the screen door is ajar as it was before, but now you can see that the door, also, is not fully closed. You feel justified to enter the house.

[[You announce yourself and push into the house->action-enter-kitchen]]

:: action-enter-kitchen
<<set $chapter to "bernadette">>\
You are in, what appears to be, the kitchen of the Lancaster house. There are some appliances straight in front of you and a counters to your right.
To your surprise, there is a [[woman->character-bernadette]] standing on the other side of a short kitchen counter. She looks up, surprised as well.
<<bern>>Well, hello there...officer?<</bern>>
You breate a sigh of relief and introduce yourself and the reason for your visit. The woman introduces herself as Bernadette, a neighbor who was just checking on the family as she has not seen them in church that day. 

The woman seems like what you would expect for the area - a farmer's wife for example. She is even wearing gardening gloves. She appears at ease and you see no signs that she was the figure you were pursuing, she is not out of breath and her clothes are not ruffled. 
<<you>>I saw someone in the back yard and they ran off when they saw me. Would you know who that was?<</you>>
<<bern>>No. No, I didn't see anyone - no idea on who that could have been if it weren't one of the Lancasters. I walked up the main road and straight to the side door, but it was open so I called but no one answered.<</bern>>
<<you>>Any idea where the Lancasters might be today?<</you>>
<<bern>>Oh, I think they might be at some church function. They are very active...but it was strange not seeing them today. I know they were participating in our Lenten challenge...<</bern>>
<<you>>Lenten challenge? What's that?<</you>>
You walk closer to the counter. There is actually some literature on the counter about lent and the about an event called the "Lenten Challenge".
<<bern>>Oh, it's a challenge we do every year before Easter. You give up something you like for the season of lent. The church has a list of things you can give up - like sweets, or TV, or even swearing. The Lancasters decided to give up...well, I don't know what they gave up, but they were very serious about it.<</bern>>
The woman's tone is friendly and relaxed but you sense a remaining sense of surprise about her.
<<you>>Would you like to see my identifcation Ma'am?<</you>>
You reach inside your jacket...
<<bern>>Oh, no need for that, officer. I believe you. I was just surprised to see you...but it makes sense that someone might have called with concerns as I mentioned: they didn't attend church today.<</bern>>
<<you>>When...when was the LAST time you spoke with any of the Lancasters? How many are there in the family?<</you>>
<<bern>>It's hard to say. But I did speak with one of them recently, not in person though.<</bern>>
<<you>>Which one?<</you>>
<<bern>>That is a good question. Let me think on that and I'll get back to you. It was very nice to meet you>, officer.<</bern>>
For a moment, you are distracted by some papers on the counter and you become lost in thought. What should you do next? Search the house? Search the property? There was only a few hours of sunlight left.

When you look up again, the woman is gone.
<<addinventory "??card??" "card-the-samaritan">>


